WEBVTT

00:00:10.292 --> 00:00:11.458
Kiriwo, wait!

00:00:12.667 --> 00:00:13.958
Huh?

00:00:17.375 --> 00:00:20.958
About that Grand Prize.
Well, we should go for it!

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:23.792
The grand, uh... what, now?

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:28.125
Yeah, you've got pure,
true ambition.

00:00:29.083 --> 00:00:30.917
I must say, you and I...

00:00:32.417 --> 00:00:35.042
...we're so much alike,
it's almost scary.

00:00:38.042 --> 00:00:40.375
[ASMODEUS]
Th-the Grand Prize?

00:00:40.417 --> 00:00:42.875
[IRUMA]
Yeah. So I was wondering

00:00:42.917 --> 00:00:44.792
if maybe
you'd both help out.

00:00:46.625 --> 00:00:48.375
[crying]

00:00:48.417 --> 00:00:50.000
Uh, you okay?

00:00:50.042 --> 00:00:51.833
But of course, sir!

00:00:51.875 --> 00:00:53.708
I couldn't stand
that some snarky cretins

00:00:53.750 --> 00:00:55.125
who can barely tie
their own shoes

00:00:55.167 --> 00:00:57.250
had the colossal nerve
to call your Battler

00:00:57.292 --> 00:00:58.375
"storage space!"

00:00:58.417 --> 00:00:59.500
Let us do this!

00:00:59.542 --> 00:01:01.125
Sounds so fun!

00:01:01.167 --> 00:01:03.750
Now let's go kablooey!
Yeah!

00:01:03.792 --> 00:01:05.417
Aw, thanks, you guys!

00:01:05.458 --> 00:01:06.667
-[chuckling]
-[CLARA] Kablooey!

00:01:07.667 --> 00:01:08.792
Heya!

00:01:11.583 --> 00:01:13.292
[IRUMA/ASMODEUS/CLARA]
A very good morning to you!

00:01:13.333 --> 00:01:14.625
Good morning, all.

00:01:14.667 --> 00:01:16.500
The time has finally come.

00:01:16.542 --> 00:01:18.042
Sure has!

00:01:18.083 --> 00:01:19.333
Now, the Grand Prize!

00:01:19.375 --> 00:01:21.208
We'll do whatever it takes
to get it!

00:01:21.250 --> 00:01:22.375
-Right!
-Yeah!

00:01:22.417 --> 00:01:24.292
[CLARA]
Gonna, gonna do my best!

00:01:24.333 --> 00:01:26.333
-[chuckles]
-Gonna, gonna do my best!

00:01:27.583 --> 00:01:29.542
[NARRATOR]
Iruma Suzuki, age fourteen.

00:01:29.583 --> 00:01:31.042
One day, he found himself

00:01:31.083 --> 00:01:33.000
the grandson of a demon
named Sullivan.

00:01:34.125 --> 00:01:36.375
Sullivan loves
and spoils Iruma

00:01:36.417 --> 00:01:38.958
and is even sending him
to the most prestigious school

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:40.167
in the land.

00:01:40.208 --> 00:01:42.292
But there is just one problem.

00:01:42.333 --> 00:01:44.083
The school Iruma is attending

00:01:44.125 --> 00:01:45.875
just so happens to be

00:01:45.917 --> 00:01:48.667
the demon school
known as Babyls.

00:01:48.708 --> 00:01:51.083
[IRUMA] I can't ever let them
find out I'm human,

00:01:51.125 --> 00:01:53.083
or I'm gonna get eaten
for sure!

00:03:26.958 --> 00:03:28.333
[IRUMA/ASMODEUS/CLARA]
"Party Eve."

00:03:30.417 --> 00:03:33.250
[BOY 1] Sweet apples!
Get your sweet apples, here!

00:03:33.292 --> 00:03:35.125
[GIRL]
We've got cotton candy!

00:03:35.167 --> 00:03:37.500
-[BOY 2] Whoa! I caught it!
-[BOY 3] Wow! Nice job!

00:03:37.542 --> 00:03:40.542
This is the official kickoff
of the long-awaited Party Eve

00:03:40.583 --> 00:03:42.542
of our school's biggest
and favorite event,

00:03:42.583 --> 00:03:43.958
the Battler Party!

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:46.000
Now let's all have a blast,
what do you say?!

00:03:46.042 --> 00:03:48.333
[STUDENTS]
Yeah!

00:03:48.375 --> 00:03:50.417
And the Grand Prize
is up for grabs!

00:03:50.458 --> 00:03:52.250
[STUDENTS]
Yeah!

00:03:52.292 --> 00:03:53.875
Oh wow.

00:03:53.917 --> 00:03:56.917
FYI, our show begins
after sundown.

00:03:56.958 --> 00:03:58.667
We should scout
the other Battlers' booths

00:03:58.708 --> 00:04:00.167
as we walk
around the venue.

00:04:00.208 --> 00:04:01.208
Good idea!

00:04:01.250 --> 00:04:02.958
And we can wear
cool disguises!

00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:04.417
I have some
for all of you.

00:04:04.458 --> 00:04:06.417
Are you a pink Come-Come?

00:04:06.458 --> 00:04:08.208
Not exactly subtle!

00:04:08.250 --> 00:04:10.167
Come on,
put it on already.

00:04:10.208 --> 00:04:12.667
-Why bother even scouting, then?
-It'll be fine. Put them on.

00:04:12.708 --> 00:04:14.792
I must say,
that's fresh indeed.

00:04:14.833 --> 00:04:16.875
I have to go conserve
my energy,

00:04:16.917 --> 00:04:19.542
so I'm leaving the scoutin'
to you guys, okay?

00:04:19.583 --> 00:04:20.625
[IRUMA/ASMODEUS/CLARA]
'Kay!

00:04:21.750 --> 00:04:23.167
[CAPTAIN]
Step right up!

00:04:23.208 --> 00:04:25.917
How about an ogre-sized
serving of yakisoba?

00:04:25.958 --> 00:04:28.625
It's devi irresistible!

00:04:28.667 --> 00:04:30.958
Come get it
while it's hot!

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:32.000
Now, listen up!

00:04:32.042 --> 00:04:33.583
We, the Yakisoba Battler,

00:04:33.625 --> 00:04:35.042
are going to take
the Grand Prize

00:04:35.083 --> 00:04:36.583
with our special yakisoba.

00:04:36.625 --> 00:04:38.333
-Ya got that?!
-[SQUAD] Yeah!

00:04:38.375 --> 00:04:41.417
-The size'll win the prize!
-[SQUAD] Yeah!

00:04:41.458 --> 00:04:43.583
Let's make sure folks smell
our amazing food

00:04:43.625 --> 00:04:45.167
so we get some challengers!

00:04:45.208 --> 00:04:47.083
It'll bring your mouth
to its knees!

00:04:47.125 --> 00:04:49.083
Try to eat all of it,
I dare you!

00:04:49.125 --> 00:04:51.125
[SQUAD]
Yeah, just try!

00:04:51.167 --> 00:04:53.333
[laughter]

00:04:53.375 --> 00:04:54.583
[IRUMA]
Pardon me.

00:04:54.625 --> 00:04:56.667
-[CAPTAIN] Huh?
-Can I try that?

00:04:56.708 --> 00:04:59.958
Oh, you think you can
handle that? Huh?

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:03.208
[laughing]

00:05:03.250 --> 00:05:04.458
Huh?

00:05:04.500 --> 00:05:05.958
[ALL]
Huh?

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:07.042
[exhales]

00:05:08.250 --> 00:05:10.917
Thanks for the little snack,
you guys. [humming]

00:05:10.958 --> 00:05:13.833
Uh, Captain? We don't have
any ingredients left!

00:05:13.875 --> 00:05:16.208
Is he a monster?
No, a demon!

00:05:16.250 --> 00:05:17.750
-[stall crashes]
-[ALL crying]

00:05:17.792 --> 00:05:19.542
My, my,
that's too bad.

00:05:19.583 --> 00:05:21.250
Master Iruma could eat
twice that amount

00:05:21.292 --> 00:05:23.167
in the blink of an eye.

00:05:23.208 --> 00:05:24.958
Oh, that was so good!

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:27.583
-[laughing]
-Hmm?

00:05:27.625 --> 00:05:28.792
Hey, Sabnock.

00:05:28.833 --> 00:05:29.875
[SABNOCK]
That was some truly

00:05:29.917 --> 00:05:31.417
first-rate eating,
my rival.

00:05:31.458 --> 00:05:34.625
Though it's too bad,
I shall take the Grand Prize!

00:05:34.667 --> 00:05:36.250
What are you getting at?

00:05:36.292 --> 00:05:39.375
Our Magical Apparatus Battler
is who will reign supreme!

00:05:39.417 --> 00:05:40.542
[electricity crackling]

00:05:40.583 --> 00:05:42.375
[BOTH growl]

00:05:42.417 --> 00:05:43.958
Easy, easy,

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:45.042
It can slide.

00:05:45.083 --> 00:05:46.375
The Party Eve is meant

00:05:46.417 --> 00:05:48.417
to be enjoyed, after all.

00:05:48.458 --> 00:05:50.500
The instructors won't be judging
the Battlers

00:05:50.542 --> 00:05:52.708
until the Party Day
tomorrow, anyway.

00:05:52.750 --> 00:05:55.792
The Party Eve is a festival
for students to have fun

00:05:55.833 --> 00:05:58.375
and ease into preparation
for tomorrow.

00:05:58.417 --> 00:06:01.542
So what are you planning to do
for the Party Day, Sabnock?

00:06:01.583 --> 00:06:04.208
Ah. An outstanding query.

00:06:04.250 --> 00:06:07.250
I shall perform an action scene
about the Demon King!

00:06:07.292 --> 00:06:10.125
We're enacting an anecdote
about a former Demon King!

00:06:10.167 --> 00:06:13.125
It'll be a massacre that
will get your blood boiling!

00:06:13.167 --> 00:06:15.792
And, of course, I am playing
the Demon King!

00:06:15.833 --> 00:06:18.833
[CLARA] Woo-hoo!
Great casting! [giggles]

00:06:18.875 --> 00:06:22.000
What?! Master Iruma is far
better suited for that role!

00:06:22.042 --> 00:06:23.708
[laughs]

00:06:23.750 --> 00:06:26.958
So you see, my Battler
shall win the Grand Prize!

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:29.083
[BOY] Well then,
challenge accepted!

00:06:29.125 --> 00:06:30.292
Oh?

00:06:30.333 --> 00:06:31.417
-[IRUMA/ASMODEUS] Hmm?
-[CLARA] Huh?

00:06:32.667 --> 00:06:34.542
-Yo.
-Classmate.

00:06:34.583 --> 00:06:35.750
What's up, Jazz?

00:06:35.792 --> 00:06:37.042
Our whole class is here!

00:06:37.083 --> 00:06:38.792
[GOEMON]
Festival time.

00:06:38.833 --> 00:06:40.250
[SCHNEIDER]
Life is a party.

00:06:40.292 --> 00:06:41.458
What they said!

00:06:41.500 --> 00:06:42.875
[CAMUI]
How very exciting.

00:06:42.917 --> 00:06:43.792
[LEAD]
Heya!

00:06:43.833 --> 00:06:45.917
Yay! The gang's all here!

00:06:45.958 --> 00:06:47.042
[laughs]

00:06:47.083 --> 00:06:48.417
We were all wandering,

00:06:48.458 --> 00:06:49.958
and somehow we bumped
into each other.

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:51.125
[LEAD/SCHNEIDER/GOEMON/PICERO]
Somehow.

00:06:51.167 --> 00:06:52.333
It wasn't merely somehow,

00:06:52.375 --> 00:06:53.583
I believe it was fate!

00:06:53.625 --> 00:06:54.917
I love you.

00:06:54.958 --> 00:06:57.208
Shall we all sample
this intriguing dish

00:06:57.250 --> 00:06:59.083
I recently acquired? Hup!

00:07:02.958 --> 00:07:05.083
[yells]

00:07:05.125 --> 00:07:06.292
[exhales]

00:07:08.833 --> 00:07:11.958
Come on, everybody,
you should all have some!

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:13.833
[ALL]
Thanks! Let's dig in!

00:07:15.375 --> 00:07:16.292
Yummy!

00:07:16.333 --> 00:07:17.708
As they say,

00:07:17.750 --> 00:07:19.333
I eat, therefore I am.

00:07:19.375 --> 00:07:22.083
Which Battler did you decide
to join, Jazz?

00:07:22.125 --> 00:07:24.042
[gulps]

00:07:24.083 --> 00:07:25.708
The New Magic Battler.

00:07:25.750 --> 00:07:26.917
Just as the name says,

00:07:26.958 --> 00:07:28.958
we're creating
all new magic

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:32.458
and presenting something
completely new as well.

00:07:32.500 --> 00:07:34.792
We're gonna generate water
from a rock!

00:07:37.167 --> 00:07:38.208
[water drips]

00:07:38.250 --> 00:07:41.167
-[IRUMA] Wow.
-[CLASS] Whoa!

00:07:41.208 --> 00:07:43.292
I'm not trying to be
a braggart or anything,

00:07:43.333 --> 00:07:45.667
but I'm pretty sure
it's gonna be awesome.

00:07:45.708 --> 00:07:48.333
I see they're going to be
rather formidable foes.

00:07:48.375 --> 00:07:49.708
I wanna see!

00:07:49.750 --> 00:07:51.167
That's nothing!

00:07:51.208 --> 00:07:53.208
Our Game Battler is going
to let you experience

00:07:53.250 --> 00:07:55.125
a game hands-on
and all-in!

00:07:56.083 --> 00:07:57.958
You'll put on
a virtual sorcerer's hat

00:07:58.000 --> 00:07:59.417
and go on a quest!

00:07:59.458 --> 00:08:01.875
[IRUMA] That sounds fun!
I wanna try!

00:08:01.917 --> 00:08:05.333
But if you get too into it,
there'll be no coming back!

00:08:05.375 --> 00:08:06.417
What?

00:08:06.458 --> 00:08:08.250
Ah, dreams are better anyway.

00:08:08.292 --> 00:08:09.500
[yawns]

00:08:10.708 --> 00:08:12.000
[CAMUI]
Can I explore an island

00:08:12.042 --> 00:08:13.792
where beautiful women
will lust after me?

00:08:13.833 --> 00:08:15.792
-Nope, sorry.
-Aah!

00:08:15.833 --> 00:08:18.917
[LEAD] But you can experience
being a superstar dem-dol.

00:08:20.917 --> 00:08:24.125
I think I want to try that.
It sounds perfect for me!

00:08:24.167 --> 00:08:26.917
Why don't the three of us
make our debut together?

00:08:26.958 --> 00:08:27.958
What?

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:29.833
No way,
I couldn't possibly.

00:08:30.833 --> 00:08:32.875
Some of the other things
to look out for

00:08:32.917 --> 00:08:35.708
are the splendid
underwater circus

00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:37.500
and the Magic Beast battles.

00:08:37.542 --> 00:08:38.875
[IRUMA]
Whoa.

00:08:38.917 --> 00:08:40.333
Every Battler this year

00:08:40.375 --> 00:08:41.542
seems to have brought
their work

00:08:41.583 --> 00:08:42.917
to a whole new level.

00:08:42.958 --> 00:08:45.708
We're up against these guys?

00:08:45.750 --> 00:08:48.667
Oh yeah! We're gonna go
kablooey and then--

00:08:48.708 --> 00:08:50.333
Hey, that's a secret!

00:08:50.375 --> 00:08:51.917
-[grunts]
-[GORGON SNAKE chomps]

00:08:51.958 --> 00:08:53.833
[CLARA giggling]

00:08:53.875 --> 00:08:55.542
We're up so high!

00:08:55.583 --> 00:08:57.917
[IRUMA]
Clara! Are you okay?!

00:08:57.958 --> 00:09:00.458
Anyway, you're really gonna
have to stand out

00:09:00.500 --> 00:09:01.667
to get the Grand Prize.

00:09:01.708 --> 00:09:02.708
[gasps]

00:09:03.875 --> 00:09:04.708
[firework whistling]

00:09:04.750 --> 00:09:05.833
[firework explodes]

00:09:06.833 --> 00:09:08.958
[IRUMA]
We totally have a chance!

00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:10.458
Why are you smirking
like that?

00:09:10.500 --> 00:09:12.167
Huh? Well...

00:09:12.208 --> 00:09:14.125
[nervous laughter]

00:09:14.167 --> 00:09:16.917
[indistinct chatter]

00:09:16.958 --> 00:09:18.833
[ASMODEUS] We,
the Magical Apparatus Battler,

00:09:18.875 --> 00:09:20.167
will get the Grand Prize.

00:09:21.208 --> 00:09:22.625
Now let us be off!

00:09:22.667 --> 00:09:24.042
Come on, let's go!

00:09:24.083 --> 00:09:26.667
Yeah, wait up, you guys!
See you later.

00:09:26.708 --> 00:09:28.292
Indeed.

00:09:28.333 --> 00:09:30.875
-Iruma!
-Huh?

00:09:30.917 --> 00:09:33.292
I'm still the one who'll take
the Grand Prize,

00:09:33.333 --> 00:09:36.042
but I look forward
to your Battler's presentation.

00:09:36.083 --> 00:09:38.542
Yeah! You should!

00:09:38.583 --> 00:09:39.583
Yes.

00:09:42.042 --> 00:09:44.167
Now, let's review the plan
one more time

00:09:44.208 --> 00:09:46.167
before Kiriwo returns.

00:09:46.208 --> 00:09:48.542
It's "Strike Fast
for Certain Victory."

00:09:48.583 --> 00:09:50.542
-Strike Fast.
-Certain Party.

00:09:50.583 --> 00:09:51.792
Victory!

00:09:51.833 --> 00:09:53.083
[clear throat]

00:09:53.125 --> 00:09:54.583
Our opportune moment comes

00:09:54.625 --> 00:09:56.292
at Party Day countdown.

00:09:56.333 --> 00:09:58.000
After the Party Eve,

00:09:58.042 --> 00:09:59.958
all students gather
in the central plaza

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:02.292
to hear the bell mark
the start of Party Day.

00:10:02.333 --> 00:10:04.750
[bell tolls]

00:10:04.792 --> 00:10:07.333
The minute that bell
stops ringing...

00:10:07.375 --> 00:10:10.083
[firework whistling]

00:10:10.125 --> 00:10:11.167
[firework explodes]

00:10:12.542 --> 00:10:15.917
We'll set the fireworks off,
stealing everyone's attention.

00:10:16.917 --> 00:10:19.500
We will begin the show
with a great, big bang

00:10:19.542 --> 00:10:22.042
and then follow up with
the smaller, pretty fireworks

00:10:22.083 --> 00:10:24.000
in an orderly fashion
so we can get,

00:10:24.042 --> 00:10:26.042
and keep,
everyone's attention.

00:10:26.083 --> 00:10:27.292
Done.

00:10:27.333 --> 00:10:29.042
That is the basic summation.

00:10:29.083 --> 00:10:30.500
-Ohh!
-[IRUMA laughs]

00:10:30.542 --> 00:10:32.125
Strike first, strike fast!

00:10:32.167 --> 00:10:33.792
-Yay for party!
-Wrong!

00:10:33.833 --> 00:10:34.708
[clears throat]

00:10:35.667 --> 00:10:38.333
It's a bit far from our
location to the central plaza,

00:10:38.375 --> 00:10:40.542
but it'll be nighttime,
so the lights and sound

00:10:40.583 --> 00:10:41.917
should be enough
to hook them in.

00:10:41.958 --> 00:10:44.167
Ooh, me. Me!

00:10:44.208 --> 00:10:46.500
I wanna shoot
the fireworks off, can I?!

00:10:46.542 --> 00:10:48.417
Only Master Iruma
is qualified

00:10:48.458 --> 00:10:51.125
and worthy of handling
such a crucial task!

00:10:51.167 --> 00:10:53.208
Aw, you're such a meanie!
Boo, boo!

00:10:53.250 --> 00:10:55.333
That's alright,
Clara can do it.

00:10:55.375 --> 00:10:56.500
What are you saying?

00:10:56.542 --> 00:10:57.833
You're the only one
for the job,

00:10:57.875 --> 00:10:58.917
Iruma, sir!

00:10:58.958 --> 00:11:00.458
If you say so.

00:11:00.500 --> 00:11:02.292
[ASMODEUS]
Its construction is flawless.

00:11:02.333 --> 00:11:04.917
It's programmed to fire
the rockets exactly ten seconds

00:11:04.958 --> 00:11:06.875
after the fuse is lit.

00:11:06.917 --> 00:11:09.792
I will provide
the official flame to start...

00:11:09.833 --> 00:11:11.375
-[flame whooshing]
-...and then, Master,

00:11:11.417 --> 00:11:13.167
you can light the fuse!

00:11:13.208 --> 00:11:15.833
-[CLARA] Like this?
-Yes, exactly! Just like--

00:11:15.875 --> 00:11:16.958
Hmm? Aah!

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:18.958
[giggles]
It's lit.

00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:20.708
[IRUMA/ASMODEUS]
Huhhh?!

00:11:20.750 --> 00:11:23.333
-[BOTH scream]
-Put it out! Quickly now!

00:11:24.708 --> 00:11:26.750
[grunting]

00:11:26.792 --> 00:11:29.208
-It won't go out!
-Get down!

00:11:29.250 --> 00:11:30.458
[ALL grunt]

00:11:33.167 --> 00:11:35.250
[smoke hissing]

00:11:35.292 --> 00:11:36.958
Huh? Misfire?

00:11:38.458 --> 00:11:41.417
Huhh! Thank goodness
for that.

00:11:41.458 --> 00:11:44.167
I truly feared
the worst had happened.

00:11:44.208 --> 00:11:46.667
Hey! Wait,
did I do something wrong?

00:11:46.708 --> 00:11:48.708
You did everything wrong!

00:11:48.750 --> 00:11:51.458
We were supposed to wait
until the Party Day begins!

00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:53.708
I just finished
explaining that!

00:11:53.750 --> 00:11:55.167
[frustrated grunt]

00:11:55.208 --> 00:11:57.125
-Oh, yeah!
-[IRUMA/ASMODEUS groan]

00:11:57.167 --> 00:11:58.667
Don't "oh yeah" me!

00:11:58.708 --> 00:11:59.792
I'm so sorry!

00:11:59.833 --> 00:12:01.500
-Not good enough!
-Now, now.

00:12:01.542 --> 00:12:04.292
You should've let us know
the shell wasn't in there!

00:12:04.333 --> 00:12:07.417
Huh? Well, I don't know
anything about that.

00:12:07.458 --> 00:12:10.625
But we obviously put
the shell in there, right?

00:12:11.583 --> 00:12:13.792
Yeah, where could the shell
have gone, though?

00:12:16.875 --> 00:12:17.958
[grunts]

00:12:18.000 --> 00:12:20.042
Oh boy.
[sighs]

00:12:20.083 --> 00:12:22.583
I can't believe how heavy
this thing is.

00:12:22.625 --> 00:12:24.500
I can barely even stand.

00:12:26.917 --> 00:12:28.000
Now, then...

00:12:30.375 --> 00:12:32.750
...it's time to kick off
our last party.

00:12:57.500 --> 00:13:00.750
[SULLIVAN] Are we still dragging
this interrogation out, boys?

00:13:00.792 --> 00:13:02.417
[OFFICER]
Investigations involving humans

00:13:02.458 --> 00:13:03.917
can get quite complex.

00:13:03.958 --> 00:13:05.583
It'll take a while,
I'm afraid.

00:13:06.542 --> 00:13:09.208
I see.
In that case, check!

00:13:09.250 --> 00:13:10.917
-Huh?
-[crying]

00:13:10.958 --> 00:13:14.875
-Yay! Too bad I win!
-I lost again!

00:13:14.917 --> 00:13:16.208
Please! One more time!

00:13:16.250 --> 00:13:17.792
Just one more game!
Please, come on!

00:13:17.833 --> 00:13:20.125
I promise this will be
the last game! Oh, come on--

00:13:20.167 --> 00:13:21.458
Honestly.

00:13:22.792 --> 00:13:24.958
He seems like
a peaceful fellow, but...

00:13:26.583 --> 00:13:28.292
...according to our intel,

00:13:28.333 --> 00:13:30.542
he illegally entered
the human world

00:13:30.583 --> 00:13:32.417
and is holding
a human teenager

00:13:32.458 --> 00:13:33.833
against his will.

00:13:34.958 --> 00:13:37.292
Is this correct, Baal?

00:13:37.333 --> 00:13:38.833
Who can say?

00:13:40.208 --> 00:13:41.667
Baal.

00:13:41.708 --> 00:13:43.042
Yeah, yeah.

00:13:43.083 --> 00:13:45.333
That's the story
my trusty little birdie told me,

00:13:45.375 --> 00:13:47.083
and I'm sticking to it.

00:13:47.125 --> 00:13:49.333
Besides, you have
your own intel, right?

00:13:51.917 --> 00:13:54.792
That's why you've got all
these guards hanging around.

00:13:54.833 --> 00:13:58.333
What is this, anyway,
your own personal goon squad?

00:13:58.375 --> 00:14:02.333
[ALL grumbling]

00:14:02.375 --> 00:14:05.208
They're here in case
he tries to escape.

00:14:05.250 --> 00:14:07.458
We need to have
all relevant parties here

00:14:07.500 --> 00:14:09.458
until his name is cleared.

00:14:09.500 --> 00:14:11.792
Although, I agree
it's rather rude

00:14:11.833 --> 00:14:14.458
to keep Lord Sullivan here
for too long.

00:14:14.500 --> 00:14:17.625
So, then, what to do,
I wonder.

00:14:17.667 --> 00:14:19.708
Might as well take
your time.

00:14:19.750 --> 00:14:22.167
If this comes to nothing,
all the better.

00:14:23.542 --> 00:14:26.750
Though, if I'm being
totally frank with you,

00:14:26.792 --> 00:14:28.917
this might very well be
what some call

00:14:28.958 --> 00:14:30.708
the calm before the storm.

00:14:36.042 --> 00:14:38.000
[AMERI]
Where the devil did Iruma go?

00:14:38.042 --> 00:14:39.583
It's already sundown.

00:14:39.625 --> 00:14:42.667
I hope he's actually prepared
for his big surprise.

00:14:45.667 --> 00:14:46.958
[giggles]

00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:48.458
I'm finally going to see
that scene

00:14:48.500 --> 00:14:50.750
from the forbidden texts
in real life.

00:14:50.792 --> 00:14:53.458
We've now patrolled
this area extensively.

00:14:53.500 --> 00:14:55.708
Uh, yes, very good!

00:14:55.750 --> 00:14:57.458
You seem distressed, Boss.

00:14:57.500 --> 00:14:59.083
Is there something
bothering you?

00:14:59.125 --> 00:15:00.750
No! I'm fine!

00:15:00.792 --> 00:15:02.292
There's nothing wrong.

00:15:02.333 --> 00:15:04.583
But given how exposed
these kinds of events are,

00:15:04.625 --> 00:15:06.708
trouble could be just
around the corner.

00:15:06.750 --> 00:15:08.250
Let's all be
on our guard.

00:15:08.292 --> 00:15:09.875
Understood.

00:15:09.917 --> 00:15:12.125
You scared me
a little bit, there.

00:15:12.167 --> 00:15:13.750
If you get it, let's go.

00:15:13.792 --> 00:15:15.042
[ALL]
Yes, boss!

00:15:16.667 --> 00:15:19.125
[AMERI]
Honestly, this is so silly.

00:15:19.167 --> 00:15:20.750
What am I even doing?!

00:15:20.792 --> 00:15:23.208
I need to focus
on my duties more.

00:15:23.250 --> 00:15:25.542
And, Iruma,
you should do the same.

00:15:27.250 --> 00:15:28.292
[EIKO]
Want to go here next?

00:15:28.333 --> 00:15:29.417
It says we can interact

00:15:29.458 --> 00:15:31.292
with some friendly
Magic Beasts.

00:15:31.333 --> 00:15:33.667
[GAAKO] Ew, I don't like
Magic Beasts.

00:15:33.708 --> 00:15:36.375
They're sorta smelly
and might bite you.

00:15:36.417 --> 00:15:38.583
[slurping]

00:15:38.625 --> 00:15:41.917
[EIKO] Hey, you think Iruma
might like Magic Beasts?

00:15:41.958 --> 00:15:44.875
Um, I think most boys do,
actually.

00:15:44.917 --> 00:15:47.625
So you're saying we could
probably run into him there!

00:15:47.667 --> 00:15:48.833
Oh yay!

00:15:48.875 --> 00:15:50.542
Where'd Kiriwo go?

00:15:50.583 --> 00:15:52.083
We need to find him soon!

00:15:53.042 --> 00:15:54.167
Iruma, sir!

00:15:55.542 --> 00:15:57.417
He's nowhere
to be found.

00:15:57.458 --> 00:15:59.125
I've checked
all the obvious places

00:15:59.167 --> 00:16:01.542
like the cafeteria
and the inner courtyard.

00:16:01.583 --> 00:16:03.167
I see.

00:16:03.208 --> 00:16:04.667
I peeked into
the Battler room,

00:16:04.708 --> 00:16:06.625
but he wasn't there either.

00:16:06.667 --> 00:16:08.375
Where could he have gone?

00:16:08.417 --> 00:16:11.042
Probably went to the Party Eve
all by himself!

00:16:11.083 --> 00:16:13.458
-It's not fair!
-Ugh, you did the same thing!

00:16:13.500 --> 00:16:14.625
Will you knock it off?!

00:16:14.667 --> 00:16:16.292
I swear it,
I was looking for him

00:16:16.333 --> 00:16:18.042
while I was fooling around!

00:16:18.083 --> 00:16:19.583
-Let me go!
-[laughs]

00:16:19.625 --> 00:16:22.792
Perhaps it would help us
to broaden our search, yes?

00:16:22.833 --> 00:16:26.375
[IRUMA] But he couldn't have
gotten far with the shell.

00:16:26.417 --> 00:16:28.333
He doesn't have
that much stamina.

00:16:28.375 --> 00:16:29.833
[grunts]

00:16:29.875 --> 00:16:31.875
Maybe he really did
run away, then.

00:16:33.542 --> 00:16:36.500
It's possible he decided
that the fireworks would fail

00:16:36.542 --> 00:16:38.333
and had a last-minute
panic attack.

00:16:38.375 --> 00:16:39.708
How dare he?!

00:16:39.750 --> 00:16:42.333
If he did,
it'll set back our launch.

00:16:42.375 --> 00:16:43.958
-[IRUMA] Don't worry.
-[ASMODEUS/CLARA] Huh?

00:16:44.000 --> 00:16:46.833
We don't know for sure it was
Kiriwo who took it.

00:16:46.875 --> 00:16:48.000
Besides...

00:16:54.583 --> 00:16:57.000
...he believes in achieving
his goals fair and square.

00:16:57.042 --> 00:16:58.500
He wouldn't do that!

00:16:58.542 --> 00:17:00.125
Everything's gonna be fine!

00:17:03.542 --> 00:17:04.917
Yes, you're right.

00:17:06.917 --> 00:17:10.292
So, Azz, Clara,
let's wait.

00:17:10.333 --> 00:17:12.000
Because we all believe
in our friend!

00:17:12.042 --> 00:17:14.958
-Yeah! Yeah! Yeah!
-Indeed.

00:17:30.833 --> 00:17:32.000
[BAAL]
Kiriwo.

00:17:33.250 --> 00:17:35.958
You sure hold one hell
of a grudge, kid.

00:17:36.000 --> 00:17:38.417
Or... is it drive?

00:17:40.208 --> 00:17:41.750
Do you think so?

00:17:41.792 --> 00:17:44.500
[chuckles]
You are so warped.

00:17:44.542 --> 00:17:48.167
It's gruesome how you wear
that smile on the outside

00:17:48.208 --> 00:17:50.542
but are rotten to the core
on the inside.

00:17:50.583 --> 00:17:52.292
[laughs]

00:17:52.333 --> 00:17:54.333
Such harsh words,
Big Bro!

00:17:55.458 --> 00:17:57.417
[BAAL] At least
you're straightforward.

00:17:57.458 --> 00:17:59.958
Don't get me wrong,
you're twisted as hell,

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:01.917
but you're always
completely candid.

00:18:03.750 --> 00:18:06.292
Most of all,
you're not wrong.

00:18:06.333 --> 00:18:08.833
It's a great reminder

00:18:08.875 --> 00:18:11.833
of the one and only way
a demon should behave!

00:18:13.625 --> 00:18:16.375
I'll prepare the stage
for you, Kiriwo.

00:18:16.417 --> 00:18:19.292
Take that ambition you've got
packed in your throat

00:18:19.333 --> 00:18:21.000
and set it free!

00:18:21.042 --> 00:18:22.250
[gasps]

00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:30.125
It's here, Big Bro.

00:18:30.167 --> 00:18:31.875
My time's come.

00:18:31.917 --> 00:18:34.375
[stretching]

00:18:34.417 --> 00:18:37.917
I am so thrilled.
Everything ends today.

00:18:39.208 --> 00:18:40.250
Or does it?

00:18:41.583 --> 00:18:43.833
No, it's just starting.

00:18:43.875 --> 00:18:46.875
[STUDENTS chattering]

00:18:54.167 --> 00:18:55.833
Maybe it's the lighting,
but somehow

00:18:55.875 --> 00:18:59.208
the boys always look cooler
than usual at these events.

00:18:59.250 --> 00:19:00.333
Yeah, I get that!

00:19:00.375 --> 00:19:02.625
Asmodeus is the only demon
for me!

00:19:06.167 --> 00:19:07.625
[seething]

00:19:07.667 --> 00:19:10.042
Taking too long!
Pay me now!

00:19:12.542 --> 00:19:14.083
[GOEMON grunting]

00:19:14.125 --> 00:19:16.167
Don't stop,
keep 'em coming!

00:19:16.208 --> 00:19:18.708
I can slice things
till my arms fall off!

00:19:18.750 --> 00:19:20.083
[SCHNEIDER]
Believe the magic!

00:19:20.125 --> 00:19:22.167
Where there's a will,
there's a way!

00:19:24.167 --> 00:19:26.250
Hey, Professor!
Do you wanna try one?

00:19:26.292 --> 00:19:27.292
[ROBIN]
Cool!

00:19:27.333 --> 00:19:29.417
Thanks,
they look delicious!

00:19:30.375 --> 00:19:32.375
No way I can eat
all this alone.

00:19:32.417 --> 00:19:33.542
[growls]

00:19:34.667 --> 00:19:36.875
-Banana, Acting Chair-Demon?
-No!

00:19:36.917 --> 00:19:39.542
Aww, come on! Aww!

00:19:39.583 --> 00:19:41.792
[chomps]
Hey, wait for me!

00:19:42.750 --> 00:19:44.750
-[CLARA] Iruma-kins!
-[laughs]

00:19:44.792 --> 00:19:47.792
Yahoo! Hurry! Hurry!

00:19:47.833 --> 00:19:50.333
Sure!
[laughing]

00:19:53.958 --> 00:19:55.708
[BAAL]
Kiriwo,

00:19:55.750 --> 00:19:58.667
you're not wrong
about any of this.

00:19:58.708 --> 00:20:00.208
Now do your duty!

00:20:04.125 --> 00:20:05.917
[shatters]

00:20:05.958 --> 00:20:09.167
-Hmm?
-[explosion booms]

00:20:09.208 --> 00:20:11.708
[ALL screaming]

00:20:13.708 --> 00:20:15.417
[screams]

00:20:15.458 --> 00:20:16.792
What in the world?!

00:20:16.833 --> 00:20:17.917
[screams]

00:20:17.958 --> 00:20:19.667
-[ALL screaming]
-[explosion booms]

00:20:19.708 --> 00:20:21.667
Oh no!

00:20:21.708 --> 00:20:24.458
[whimpering]

00:20:24.500 --> 00:20:25.417
[ALL]
Huh?

00:20:25.458 --> 00:20:28.208
[straining]

00:20:30.250 --> 00:20:32.167
[ALL fawning]

00:20:32.208 --> 00:20:35.250
My, aren't you just
the bravest?

00:20:46.250 --> 00:20:47.875
Hey! What just happened?

00:20:47.917 --> 00:20:49.708
[GIRL]
What's going on?!

00:20:49.750 --> 00:20:51.792
That was really terrifying.

00:20:51.833 --> 00:20:53.500
[snoring]

00:20:53.542 --> 00:20:55.958
Quickly, ladies!
To my side, at once!

00:20:57.500 --> 00:21:00.208
Calm down! Make sure the
students and staff are alright!

00:21:00.250 --> 00:21:02.708
All faculty should check
their stations! Hurry!

00:21:02.750 --> 00:21:04.208
Yes, sir!

00:21:04.250 --> 00:21:06.000
That means
you too, Robin. Go!

00:21:06.042 --> 00:21:09.125
No! I'm staying here and
helping you, Acting Chair-Demon!

00:21:09.167 --> 00:21:10.667
[grumbles]

00:21:10.708 --> 00:21:12.458
Oh wow!

00:21:12.500 --> 00:21:15.000
That was...
What happened?!

00:21:15.042 --> 00:21:17.583
Azz, Clara!
You both okay?

00:21:17.625 --> 00:21:19.458
-Yes, sir!
-Totally fine!

00:21:19.500 --> 00:21:20.750
Oh good.

00:21:21.750 --> 00:21:23.833
Looks like everyone else
is okay, too.

00:21:23.875 --> 00:21:25.542
What even was that?

00:21:25.583 --> 00:21:28.333
I have no idea, but we should
probably get out--

00:21:28.375 --> 00:21:29.583
[ASMODEUS/CLARA gasp]

00:21:29.625 --> 00:21:31.583
-[ASMODEUS] Iruma, sir!
-That hurt.

00:21:31.625 --> 00:21:33.000
What happened to you?

00:21:33.042 --> 00:21:35.833
It sounds crazy,
but... it felt

00:21:35.875 --> 00:21:37.333
like I bumped
into something.

00:21:37.375 --> 00:21:39.875
Huh? But I don't see any...

00:21:41.625 --> 00:21:42.625
[gasps]

00:21:44.708 --> 00:21:47.083
There's a wall,
and it's invisible.

00:21:47.125 --> 00:21:48.583
Yeah, you're right!

00:21:48.625 --> 00:21:50.750
-Something's there!
-[BOY 1] What's going on?

00:21:50.792 --> 00:21:52.583
[BOY 2] There are
invisible walls everywhere!

00:21:52.625 --> 00:21:54.125
[BOY 3]
Are we trapped inside?

00:21:54.167 --> 00:21:56.125
[GIRL]
Wait, seriously?

00:21:56.167 --> 00:21:57.417
[BOY 4]
What the hell?!

00:21:57.458 --> 00:21:58.875
Why are we blocked off?!

00:21:58.917 --> 00:22:00.000
Is this...

00:22:06.958 --> 00:22:08.667
[KIRIWO]
Hmm. Now, then...

00:22:09.750 --> 00:22:11.917
...let's get
the real party started!

00:23:45.917 --> 00:23:47.833
Su... Ki... Ma.

00:23:48.792 --> 00:23:50.083
[ASMODEUS]
There's an invisible wall

00:23:50.125 --> 00:23:52.250
separating Master Iruma
and me!

00:23:52.292 --> 00:23:55.125
He's so close
and yet so far away!

00:23:55.167 --> 00:23:57.542
I'm right here, yet I can't be
of service to him!

00:23:57.583 --> 00:23:58.917
[crying]
Oh why?!

00:23:58.958 --> 00:24:00.458
Aw, don't cry, Azz!

00:24:00.500 --> 00:24:02.625
[crying]

00:24:02.667 --> 00:24:03.792
Not you, too!

00:24:03.833 --> 00:24:05.125
I see,
you must be sad

00:24:05.167 --> 00:24:06.458
about being cruelly separated

00:24:06.500 --> 00:24:08.417
from Master Iruma, too.

00:24:08.458 --> 00:24:10.833
Ahhh! For once,
we are true comrades!

00:24:10.875 --> 00:24:13.958
My takoyaki's
gonna get cold!

00:24:14.958 --> 00:24:16.417
Eiko here,

00:24:16.458 --> 00:24:18.958
and my first Battler Party's
been amazing!

00:24:19.000 --> 00:24:20.542
The only thing
that would be better

00:24:20.583 --> 00:24:23.250
is geting c-closer to Iruma.

00:24:23.292 --> 00:24:24.500
I-Iruma!

00:24:24.542 --> 00:24:25.792
I'm going to muster up
the courage

00:24:25.833 --> 00:24:27.417
to call your name!

00:24:27.458 --> 00:24:29.417
Iru-- Ow!

00:24:29.458 --> 00:24:31.667
What is this,
an invisible wall?

00:24:31.708 --> 00:24:35.667
Next time,
"Run, Iruma, to Kiriwo!"

00:24:35.708 --> 00:24:37.417
Iruma's running away!

00:24:37.458 --> 00:24:38.917
Wait, come back!

00:24:38.958 --> 00:24:41.042
